        <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;iterative-brute-force&#34;&gt;Iterative Brute Force
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p&gt;Given an array of integers &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt; and an integer &lt;code&gt;target&lt;/code&gt;, return the indices of the two numbers
such that they add up to &lt;code&gt;target&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;process&#34;&gt;Process
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Descend through &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt;, iterating from index &lt;code&gt;0&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Within the first loop, descend through &lt;code&gt;nums&lt;/code&gt; once more, this time iterating from index &lt;code&gt;1&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the difference of &lt;code&gt;target&lt;/code&gt; and the inner value equals the outer value, return each index.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If both loops complete without a successful comparison, return empty.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
